					<physDesc rend="visible">
						<p>Parchment codex; Ashkenazi punctuated square and unpunctuated semi-cursive script.</p>
						<objectDesc form="codex">
							<supportDesc material="perg">
								<support>Parchment codex.</support>
								<extent>40 folios <dimensions unit="mm" type="leaf">
										<height>350</height>
										<width>255</width>
									</dimensions>
									<dimensions type="written" unit="mm">
										<height>250</height>
										<width>170</width>
									</dimensions>
								</extent>
								<foliation>
									<p>40 folios (+ 2 paper flyleaves at the beginning and 1 older and 3 modern paper flyleaves at the end).</p>
								</foliation>
								<collation>
									<p>11 quires: i-ii4-1 (folios 1-6), iii2 (folios 7-8), iv-xi4 (folios 9-40).</p>
								</collation>
							</supportDesc>
							<layoutDesc>
								<layout columns="1" ruledLines="10 60" writtenLines="10 60">
									<p>Ruling and sometimes pricking are visible. </p>
									<p>Watermark, folio [41v], of a fleur-de-lis, unidentified. </p>
									<p>The square and semi-cursive scripts are imitations of the Amsterdam letters and Rashi script respectively used in printing.</p>
								</layout>
							</layoutDesc>
